Voice-Controlled AI Assistant

This Python script implements a simple voice-controlled AI assistant using the pyttsx3 text-to-speech library and the speech_recognition library for speech recognition.
  The assistant can perform tasks such as providing the current time, searching Wikipedia, opening Google, and launching Visual Studio Code. Additionally, 
it can dynamically play songs from YouTube based on user input.

Features:

Text-to-speech and speech recognition functionalities.
Dynamic song playback using pywhatkit.playonyt.
Basic commands for searching Wikipedia, opening Google, checking the time, and opening VS Code.
Usage:

Install required libraries: pip install pyttsx3 speech_recognition wikipedia pywhatkit.
Run the script: python main.py.
Interact with the assistant using voice commands.
